This paper is about a novel optimizer for deep neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on optimization methods, which suggests that it is likely to fall under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions that it outperforms other optimization methods on large-scale high-dimensional machine learning problems, which suggests that it could also fall under the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also mentions that it provides PyTorch and TensorFlow implementations, which suggests that it could fall under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
